	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />it's quite possible that some of your controllers have a bad IC chip.
<br />I once builded a NES to PC gameport adapter and one of my
<br />4 controllers didn't worked with it, i replaced the IC chip and it worked fine.
<br />
<br />My adapter used CD4017 to emulate P/S line, 4000 series cannot produce
<br />more current than 1mA, but in real NES the P/S line output current is in fact
<br />larger.
<br />
<br />If i remember correctly, NES four score has built in autofire options,
<br />so it might be that the exhausted IC is overloading the your four player device.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


